== SCHEMA DETAILS ==

Table: api_keys
  id UUID PK DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
  key_hash TEXT NOT NULL
  label TEXT
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()

Table: identities
  id TEXT PK DEFAULT 'default'
  agent_token TEXT
  git_token TEXT
  refresh_token TEXT
  token_expires_at TIMESTAMPTZ
  git_provider TEXT
  git_base_url TEXT
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()

Table: personas
  id UUID PK DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
  name TEXT NOT NULL
  prompt TEXT NOT NULL
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()

Table: workers
  id TEXT PK
  host TEXT NOT NULL
  labels JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}'
  capabilities JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '[]'
  client_version TEXT
  last_seen_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()

Table: sessions
  id UUID PK DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
  repo_url TEXT NOT NULL
  ref TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'main'
  workflow TEXT NOT NULL
  params JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}'
  persona_id UUID REFERENCES personas(id)
  identity_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default' REFERENCES identities(id)
  status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending'
  retain_forever BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT false
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()

Table: jobs
  id UUID PK DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
  session_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES sessions(id) ON DELETE CASCADE
  worker_id TEXT REFERENCES workers(id)
  status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending'
  task_input JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}'
  error_message TEXT
  branch TEXT
  commit_ref TEXT
  mr_title TEXT
  mr_description TEXT
  pull_request_url TEXT
  output TEXT
  sentinel_reached BOOLEAN DEFAULT false
  assistant_reply TEXT
  reclaim_count INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0
  assigned_at TIMESTAMPTZ
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()

Table: logs
  id UUID PK DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
  session_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES sessions(id) ON DELETE CASCADE
  job_id UUID REFERENCES jobs(id) ON DELETE CASCADE
  worker_id TEXT
  level TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'info'
  source TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'control_plane'
  message TEXT NOT NULL
  timestamp TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()

Indexes:
  idx_logs_session_timestamp ON logs (session_id, timestamp)
  idx_logs_job_timestamp ON logs (job_id, timestamp)
  idx_jobs_session_id ON jobs (session_id)
  idx_jobs_status ON jobs (status)
  idx_jobs_worker_status ON jobs (worker_id, status)
  idx_workers_last_seen ON workers (last_seen_at)
  idx_sessions_status_created ON sessions (status, created_at)

== DESIGN DECISIONS ==

- Used TIMESTAMPTZ everywhere for timezone safety (per spec)
- JSONB columns for params, labels, capabilities, task_input (per spec)
- TEXT for status columns instead of enums for flexibility during development (per spec)
- No inbox tables yet (P1 feature, per spec)
- Single migration file since this is the initial schema
- Default DATABASE_URL points to docker-compose postgres instance
- PgPoolOptions with max_connections=5 for dev

== EXISTING CODEBASE CONTEXT ==

The project is a Rust monorepo with 4 crates:
- api-types: Shared request/response types, IDs, contracts
- server: Control plane (axum HTTP + SSE, sqlx PostgreSQL)
- worker: Worker (reqwest, git2, runs Claude Code/Cursor CLI)
- cli: CLI (clap, API client, log tail)

The api-types crate defines ID types as newtype wrappers around String (using a macro). UUID IDs in the DB map to String IDs in the API types. WorkflowType and SessionStatus are enums with snake_case serde. TaskInput is a tagged enum. All timestamps use chrono::DateTime<Utc>.

The web/ directory exists for the React + TypeScript + Vite UI but was not touched in this task.

